description: Jim O'Neill, a former investor, critic of health regulations and U.S. Health Secretary Robert F. Kennedy Jr.'s deputy, is taking control of the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention following a tumultuous week in which the agency's director was forced out.
title: RFK Jr. deputy Jim O'Neill to serve as acting leader of U.S. CDC

description: A Windsor doctor is being fined after a privacy investigation confirmed that he had inappropriately accessed patient health information to offer circumcisions at his private clinic.
title: Windsor doctor fined by Ontario privacy office after accessing health records to offer circumcision services

description: The hailstorm that slammed the Brooks area, southeast of Calgary, on Aug. 20 is expected to cost millions in crop damage alone, according to insurance providers.
title: Millions of dollars in crop damage expected from hailstorm in Brooks, Alta.

description: The Calgary man who killed himself during a three-hour standoff Thursday that began after he shot at police was facing trials on a number of organized crime-related offences and had recently cut off his ankle monitor, CBC News has learned.
title: Man found dead after shooting at Calgary police in 3-hour standoff identified as local gangster

description: Nova Scotians can return to the woods in parts of the province. Premier Tim Houston said Friday that a provincewide ban would end for some areas at 4 p.m., but the ban remains for several counties. The burn ban remains in place.
title: Woods ban lifted for parts of Nova Scotia

description: Michael Longfellow, Devon Walker and Emil Wakim all announced their departures on Instagram, while multiple outlets are reporting that longtime SNL member Heidi Gardner won’t be returning.
title: Big shakeups coming to SNL as four cast members exit the sketch show

description: After mass layoffs at banana giant Chiquita's Panama operation this summer threatened the fruit's supply chains, work is set to resume at the plant in Bocas del Toro.
title: A-peeling news for banana workers as Chiquita operations to resume in Panama

description: Montreal-based online fashion retailer Ssense plans to file for bankruptcy protection after its primary lender signaled plans to force a sale of the company in its own request for bankruptcy protection, a Ssense spokesperson told CBC News in an email.
title: Online retailer Ssense filing for bankruptcy protection

description: The stabbing of a Jewish woman in broad daylight at an Ottawa grocery store has prompted public officials, including the city's mayor, to condemn what they're calling a disturbing act of hate-motivated violence in the community.
title: 'This isn't Ottawa': Outrage grows over 'vile' grocery store attack on Jewish woman

description: The community of Behchokǫ̀, N.W.T., is setting up around 200 cots for evacuees from Whatı̀ after officials ordered Whatı̀ residents to evacuate their community due to a nearby wildfire.
title: Evacuation order issued for community of 600 northwest of Yellowknife

description: The evacuation of the community of Whatı̀, N.W.T., is proceeding in an orderly fashion by road, according to a Northwest Territories fire information officer.
title: Evacuation order issued for community of 600 northwest of Yellowknife

description: Officials in Whatı̀, N.W.T., have ordered residents to evacuate the community due to a wildfire less than 10 kilometres away.
title: Evacuation order issued for community of 600 northwest of Yellowknife

description: Conservative Leader Pierre Poilievre is calling on the federal government to amend the Criminal Code so that use of force is presumed reasonable against a person who illegally enters a house and poses a threat to those inside.
title: Poilievre calls for more legal protection for Canadians defending homes from intruders

description: Conservative Leader Pierre Poilievre is calling on the federal government to amend the Criminal Code so that the use of force is presumed reasonable when used against a person who illegally enters a house and poses a threat to people inside.
title: Poilievre calls for more legal protection for Canadians defending homes from intruders

description: Hundreds of Indonesians protested at sites across Jakarta on Friday over the death of a civilian hit by a police vehicle, triggering calls for police reform in the first major test for President Prabowo Subianto's nearly year-old government.
title: Protests erupt in Indonesia after motorcyclist killed by police vehicle in clashes

description: Yves Veggie Cuisine, a Canadian plant-based food brand that was a staple in some vegetarian and vegan households, is being discontinued after 40 years in business, its parent company told CBC News on Thursday.
title: Canadian plant-based food brand Yves Veggie Cuisine to be discontinued

description: Negotiations between Alberta teachers and the provincial government have broken down days before most kindergarten-to-Grade 12 students return to the classroom.
title: Education minister says union 'playing politics' with Alberta students over strike threat

description: The death toll in a major Russian missile and drone strike on the Ukrainian capital rose to 23, including four children, officials said Friday, as U.S.-led efforts to end the three-year war remain stuck in apparent limbo.
title: Death toll in Ukraine's capital rises to 23 after Russian attack, peace talks stalled

description: Canada's economy shrank in the second quarter by a much larger degree than expected on an annualized basis as U.S. tariffs squeezed exports. But higher household and government spending cushioned some of the impact, data showed on Friday.
title: Canadian economy shrinks 1.6% in second quarter as U.S. tariffs squeeze exports

description: Thailand's Constitutional Court on Friday dismissed Paetongtarn Shinawatra from her position as prime minister, ruling that as the country's leader she violated constitutional rules on ethics in a phone call with Cambodia's Senate President Hun Sen.
title: Thai PM Paetongtarn Shinawatra ordered removed from office over compromising phone call

description: Israel's military on Friday said it was suspending mid-day pauses to allow the delivery of humanitarian aid to Gaza City, calling it a "a dangerous combat zone."
title: Israel halts humanitarian pauses in Gaza City, declares it a 'dangerous combat zone'

description: Former South Korean prime minister Han Duck-soo was indicted on charges of abetting insurrection and committing perjury, a spokesperson for the prosecutors said in Seoul on Friday.
title: South Korea sees high-profile indictments of former PM, ex-president's wife months after political chaos

description: Divers John Brooks and Eric Peterson encountered the shark in waters near Fox Point Beach, about a 40-minute drive from Halifax.
title: Scuba divers come face to face with great white shark near Hubbards, N.S.

description: The expected cost to clean up orphan oil and natural gas wells in Alberta has surpassed one billion dollars — reaching an all-time high.
title: Cost to clean up orphan wells in Alberta reaches all-time high

description: People are using chatbots such as ChatGPT and custom-designed companion bots as emotional support or advisors on life decisions. But there is disturbing evidence they may not be able to handle serious emotional issues, and could cause harm.
title: People are turning to AI for emotional support. Are chatbots up to the job?

description: Joey Nixon, a pillar in Toronto’s tattoo scene, is saying goodbye to his iconic Queen Street shop with a few parting words for new artists stepping onto the scene.
title: Toronto tattoo vet calls out poorly-trained newbies wreaking 'havoc' on industry

description: Newfoundland and Labrador is expected to become part of Canadian space history on Friday, when the first commercial rocket launch in the country takes off from near St. Lawrence.
title: All systems go: Canada's first commercial space launch ready to take flight
